        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 3:57PM MDT by NWS Cheyenne WY</headline>
        <description>At 357 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles east of Sybille Canyon, or 22 miles southwest of Wheatland,
moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northeastern Albany
and southwestern Platte Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM MDT for
southeastern Wyoming.</instruction>
